Tried so many different Chinese food places since moving to silver spring and finally found this one! By far the best Chinese food in the area and really decently priced too.

I’ve been ordering food from this place since 2004 when they were on Fenton Street. Food has always been awesome especially the peking  duck. However, since they re-opened, after the Covid-19 shutdown, I have a strong feeling that they are under a new ownership. The last few time we’ve ordered, the food has been way off. Tonight we got the peking duck and besides being cold, it was mostly skin and barely any meat. Too bad. I miss the good food they once had.
Tried this place in the past with a friend and I am hooked since then. I liked the fantastic ambience and tasty food and beverages. 5 stars.

The best Chinese food in the Silver Spring area; they have the classics, but also an excellent vegetarian menu and healthier options as well. That said, the fried dumplings are amazing—I highly recommend them, along with the General Tso’s chicken! Also, their delivery is very prompt, and they don’t tend to underestimate the time (they usually arrive 10-20 minutes earlier, in fact).

This spot is the one I always prefer. I go to many restaurants but here I keep coming back again and again. The team is very chummy and the food they offer is so good. I would always prefer to have a good dinner in this place. I highly recommend this place.

After making an online lunch order and not receiving it, I called 3 times and spoke to 3 different people. Hours 1 & 2, the first 2 people told me my delivery was out and on the way. After 3 hours the third person told me they didn't have an order for me AT ALL and I have to take it up with the company. I ordered through THEIR website and not a third party! I had previously been pleased with them, but to wait 3 hours because I was told my food was on the way then be told I don't even have an order, and not even offer to take my order and correct the mistake has cost them to lose a loyal customer. Customer service is everything.

I USE TO LOVE GOLDEN HOUSE.  This carryout was my family's go to Chinese carryout. Last night I ordered a small shrimp fried rice. Half way through my meal I discovered a long strand of black hair (I have medium sized locs). I called Golden House to inform them and they were very understanding, apologized and delivered my meal again in like 30 minutes. I decided to have it for lunch today and guess what..ANOTHER STRAND OF LONG BLACK HAIR. How does someone mess up twice? Either way, I'm done with this place now. Dag it!

I think this is the best quick Chinese place I've ever eaten in.  I ordered Chicken with Mixed Vegetables and Roast Pork with Vegetables.  The meat was lean, not fatty.  Veggies were still crisp, colorful, and fresh, not drowning in sauce or glistening in oil.  Tasty, didn't make me ridiculously thirsty later, so I'm guessing no MSG.
